## 6. What to Avoid

### 6.1 Prohibited Phrases

| Instead of | Use |
|------------|-----|
| "Leverage" | "Use" |
| "Utilize" | "Use" |
| "Synergy" | Be specific |
| "Best practices" | "What works well" |
| "Circle back" | "Follow up" |
| "Touch base" | "Connect" or "Check in" |
| "Disrupt" | Be specific about change |
| "Game-changer" | Explain actual impact |

### 6.2 Prohibited Patterns

❌ **Fake urgency:** "Don't miss out!", "Limited time!", "Act now!"
❌ **Empty superlatives:** "Best", "Ultimate", "Perfect", "Amazing"
❌ **Manipulative framing:** "Everyone else is...", "You don't want to be..."
❌ **Over-promising:** "Guaranteed results", "Will definitely work"

### 6.3 Prohibited Structures

❌ **Clickbait headlines:** "You won't believe what happened..."
❌ **Excessive questions:** "Have you ever wondered...?"
❌ **Teaser delays:** "But first, let me tell you about..."
❌ **Unnecessary preamble:** "Before we dive in, I want to..."

