## 7. Narrative Checklist

Before publishing any content, verify:

### Truth & Accuracy
- [ ] All claims are factually accurate
- [ ] Sources cited where appropriate
- [ ] Uncertainty clearly marked
- [ ] No invented data or quotes

### Clarity & Structure
- [ ] Main point is clear within first paragraph
- [ ] Paragraphs are under 4 sentences
- [ ] Lists are used for 3+ items
- [ ] Headings guide the reader

### Tone & Voice
- [ ] Advisory, not authoritative
- [ ] Calm, not hype
- [ ] Zero filler words
- [ ] Professional-casual register

### Reader Value
- [ ] Clear takeaway or action
- [ ] Trade-offs acknowledged
- [ ] Respects reader's time
- [ ] Would Isaac sign this?

